    </para>
    <para id="id14195114">Figure 1.15 The inward collapsing spiral path of electron when emitting synchrotron radiation and the outward expanding spiral path of electron when boosted by alternating electric field.</para>
    <para id="id9659073">This classical scenario is applicable to particles traversing circular paths at macroscopic scales. This is applicable to Betatron as well as to Synchrotron. But this picture completely fails at the Atomic scale. </para>
    <para id="id14392239">For a Hydrogen Atom from Eq.(1.25) and (1.31) we obtain the following equation:</para>
    <para id="id5255754"/>
    <para id="id4033483">E = -q<sup>2</sup>/(8πε<sub>0</sub>r<sub>n</sub>)</para>
    <para id="id13095329">Multiplying numerator and denominator by r<sub>n</sub> on RHS we get:</para>
    <para id="id11094134"/>
    <para id="id9280261">E = -[q<sup>2</sup>/(8πε<sub>0</sub>r<sub>n</sub><sup>2</sup><sub/>)] ×r<sub>n</sub></para>
    <para id="id13374073">Substituting the value of r<sub>n</sub> from Eq.(1.26) we get:</para>
